  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 7 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 8 high, 6 medium, 24 normal. Key bases needing attention include Tirana International Airport Mother Teresa (TIA/LATI), Rome–Fiumicino Leonardo da Vinci (FCO/LIRF) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK); plus 6 other bases. 6 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Larnaca (LCA/LCLK) and Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ). Network hotspots: David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN), Stockholm-Arlanda (ARN/ESSA) and 2 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and approach minima limits. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Sandefjord Airport, Torp (TRF/ENTO), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN), Stockholm-Arlanda (ARN/ESSA) and 9 others.",
